The paper deals with the construction of algebraic codes and their list decoding properties, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of linear-algebraic techniques and function fields suggests a connection to algebraic geometry and number theory, which are also relevant to coding theory and could place the paper in categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CR (cryptography and security). Finally, the mention of Monte Carlo algorithms and probabilistic analysis suggests a possible connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which could place the paper in cs.SI (social and information networks).
